File: Eskom said load-shedding is scheduled at night to maximise electricity availability during the day. JOHANNESBURG - Stage 2 load-shedding will be implemented on Wednesday from 9pm to Thursday morning 8am. Eskom said load-shedding is scheduled at night to maximise electricity availability during the day. "Owing to a loss of additional generation capacity, emergency reserved had to be extensively utilised to supplement capacity during the day," Eskom said in a statement. READ: Eskom: Stage 2 load-shedding 'highly likely' "These now need to be replenished to meet Thursday's electricity demand." The utility asked customers to reduce demand.